{% block content %}
    <h1>
        Gutter Cleaning North Vancouver – Protect Your Home from
        Rain, Moss, and Water Damage</h1>
    <p>Are you a homeowner in North Vancouver, BC, between 30
        and 60+ years old? You’ve invested years of hard work
        into your home — whether it’s a hillside property in
        Upper Lonsdale, a family house in Lynn Valley, or a
        modern home near Deep Cove. In one of the greenest and
        rainiest parts of Metro Vancouver, protecting that
        investment requires more than just routine maintenance.
    </p>
    <p>Due to the nearby mountains, dense forests, and
        constant rainfall, clogged gutters are one of the most
        common and dangerous problems for local homes. At Clean
        Gutters Crew (CGC), we provide professional gutter
        cleaning that North Vancouver homeowners rely on to keep
        their properties safe, dry, and structurally sound
        year-round.</p>
    <h2>Why Neglected Gutters Are Especially Risky for North
        Vancouver Homes</h2>
    <p>North Vancouver’s environment is beautiful — but tough
        on houses. Pine needles, leaves, branches, and moss
        accumulate quickly, especially in neighborhoods
        surrounded by trees. When gutters become blocked,
        rainwater has nowhere to go and begins to overflow onto
        the roofline, siding, and foundation.</p>
    <p>This can lead to wood rot, mold growth, damaged
        roofing, basement moisture, and even structural issues
        over time. Homes located on slopes or near forests are
        particularly vulnerable, as water can be directed toward
        the foundation instead of away from it. Regular
        professional cleaning is one of the simplest ways to
        prevent expensive repairs and protect your home’s
        long-term value.</p>
    <p>Many homeowners only notice a problem after seeing
        water stains, overflowing gutters during storms, or damp
        areas around the house. By then, damage may already be
        developing behind walls or under the roof.</p>
    <h2>The Smart Solution: Professional Gutter Maintenance
        in North Vancouver</h2>
    <p>Experts recommend cleaning gutters at least twice a
        year in the Lower Mainland — once in spring and once
        after the fall leaf drop. In heavily forested areas of
        North Vancouver, more frequent maintenance may be needed
        to keep drainage systems working properly.</p>
    <h2>Here’s What You Get When You Choose Clean Gutters
        Crew (CGC):</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Complete debris removal from gutters and downspouts
        </li>
        <li>Inspection of connections, joints, and mounting
            hardware</li>
        <li>Safe, professional equipment designed for
            multi-level homes</li>
        <li>Clean work with no scattered debris left behind</li>
        <li>Fast response and convenient scheduling</li>
        <li>Transparent pricing with no hidden fees</li>
        <li>Reliable service trusted by local homeowners</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Our Careful Approach to Protecting Your Home</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Assessment of gutter condition and problem areas
        </li>
        <li>Safe setup suitable for steep roofs and hillside
            properties</li>
        <li>Thorough cleaning of gutters and removal of buildup
        </li>
        <li>Downspout check to ensure proper water flow</li>
        <li>Final cleanup so your property looks neat and tidy
        </li>
    </ol>
    <p>Whether you need a one-time cleaning after a storm or
        ongoing maintenance throughout the year, Clean Gutters
        Crew is a dependable choice for North Vancouver
        homeowners who want peace of mind.</p>
    <p>Contact us today to protect your home from water
        damage and keep it in excellent condition for years to
        come.</p>
